title: Thales Payshield 10K Utilization
agents: snmp
catalog: hw/Payshield
license: Proprietary
distribution: Proprietary
description:
 This check monitors the utilization of individual Payshield commands via SNMP. It helps you understand how frequently each command is used on the HSM.

 The check creates one service for each command to be monitored.

 Prerequisites:
 - Utilization statistics gathering must be enabled on the Payshield HSM (see Payshield console command UTILENABLE; default is enabled).
 - The measurement period for instantaneous statistics must match the check_mk check frequency (recommended: 60 seconds).
 - Configure the measurement period with UTILCFG (default: 10 seconds; recommended: 60 seconds).

 The output of the SNMP value should look like:
 60,3
 EW,00001;M0,00881;M2,00319;
 The first line shows the measurement period and the number of commands used. The second line lists each command and its usage count.

item:
 Names of the commands are configured in the monitoredcommands variable inside the check script.

perfdata:
 One graph for payshield command will be created

inventory:
 This check does not create inventory entries.

